@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "BSIT 3-1 Class Schedule Management System";
}
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>@ViewData["Title"]</title>

  
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:wght@300;400;600&family=Roboto:wght@400;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

  
    <style>
        body {
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;
            color: #333;
        }

        h1 {
            text-align: center;
            margin-top: 30px;
            font-size: 2.5rem;
            color: #4A90E2;
            font-weight: 600;
        }

        p {
            max-width: 900px;
            margin: 20px auto;
            font-size: 1.2rem;
            line-height: 1.8;
            text-align: justify;
            padding: 15px;
            background-color: #fff;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0px 4px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }

        span.subject {
            font-weight: 600;
            color: #E94E77;
            font-family: 'Roboto', sans-serif;
        }

        footer {
            text-align: center;
            margin-top: 50px;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            color: #777;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

    <p>
        The BSIT 3-1 Class Schedule is structured to provide students with a balanced mix of theoretical and practical subjects across three key days:
        <span class="subject">Wednesday</span>, <span class="subject">Thursday</span>, and <span class="subject">Saturday</span>. <br />
        Wednesdays are filled with diverse courses, starting with <span class="subject">(IT Elective)</span> in the morning,
        followed by <span class="subject">(Fundamentals of Research)</span> in the afternoon, and concluding with <span class="subject">(Art Appreciation)</span> in the evening. <br />
        Thursdays focus heavily on technical skills, featuring an extended morning session for <span class="subject">(Web Development)</span> and a comprehensive afternoon class for
        <span class="subject">(Multimedia)</span>. <br />
        Saturdays are dedicated to core IT topics, beginning with <span class="subject">(System Integration & Architecture 1)</span> in the morning, and wrapping up with an afternoon-to-evening session on
        <span class="subject">(Data Administration)</span>. This schedule ensures that students have ample time to engage deeply with each subject while also balancing academic demands with personal time.
    </p>

    <footer>
        © 2024 BSIT 3-1 Class Schedule Management System. All rights reserved.
    </footer>

</body>
</html>
